@@ -0,0 +1,55 @@
+# WFM Demand Module (Prototype)
+
+Backend: ASP.NET Core Web API + SQL Server 2019  
+Frontend: React + TypeScript (Vite) + MUI + TanStack Query + Recharts
+
+## Backend
+1) Configure DB connection string in `src/Wfm.DemandModule.Api/appsettings.json` or via environment variable:
+   ConnectionStrings__DemandDb = "Server=...;Database=...;..."
+2) Run SQL scripts in `sql/001_create_schema.sql` and optional seed `sql/002_seed_demo_data.sql`.
+3) Run API from Visual Studio (F5). Swagger: https://localhost:{port}/swagger
+
+### Get token (prototype)
+POST /api/v1/auth/token
+{ "userId": "jonas", "role": "Admin" }
+
+Authorize in Swagger: Bearer {token}
+
+## Frontend
+1) cd frontend
+2) npm install
+3) npm run dev
+4) Open http://localhost:5173
+
+Paste JWT token in the top bar and click "Save token".
+
+## Notes
+- CORS is enabled for localhost:5173 (prototype only).
+